<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1911/529266-625x325.jpg?2" alt="Photo by GCIS. Shared by GovernmentZA on ." width="625" height="325">Photo by GCIS. Shared by GovernmentZA on flickr.Ramaphosa’s withdrawal, announced less than an hour before the show was due to start, comes just as South Africa starts its annual 16 Days of No Violence Against Women and Children campaign. Mkhari and his wife, Ipeleng, were arrested in 2018 after raising charges of assault against each other. Those were later withdrawn.“The Presidency emphasises that the non-participation of President Ramaphosa should not be read as an endorsement of the untested allegations raised by the civil society organisations but a carefully weighed up decision taken in the public interest,” his office said.Read more on Daily Maverick.